title: London Rock Symphony - Moses and the Impossible Ten (1973 quad m
description:
London Rock Symphony - Moses and the Impossible Ten (1973 quad mix 24/96 lossless 4.0 DVD-A)

24/96 4.0 lossless MLP (DVD-Audio).
16/48 4.0 AC3 @ 440kbps (DVD-Video) for compatibility with standard DVD players.
Flat transfer with slight noise/crackle filtering applied (Izotope RX 3), no EQ, dynamic range compression, or rear channel boost.

Converted from quad QS encoded vinyl using a SANSUI QS-D1000 VARIO MATRIX hardware decoder.


Note: This is an obscure early seventies rock opera possibly inspired by Jesus Christ Superstar, that AFAIK has never been released on CD. The bass players name is listed as John Paul Jones. Not surprisingly dishonest eBay sellers claim it's the Led Zeppelin bassist. I have never seen this album on any JPJ/LZ discography anywhere, so it's highly likely to be another person with the same name.
